sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant KServe as KServe Router<br/>(Platform TLS/Auth)
    participant API as vLLM OpenAI API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Runner as HPUModelRunner<br/>(vllm-gaudi plugin)
    participant HPU as Intel Gaudi HPU<br/>(Synapse AI)
    participant Peers as Peer Gaudi Workers<br/>(HCCL/RDMA)
    participant Storage as Model Storage<br/>S3/PVC/HuggingFace<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 1: Model Loading (startup)
    API->>Storage: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: HF Token / AWS IAM
    Storage-->>API: Model artifacts
    API->>Runner: Load model to HPU
    Runner->>HPU: Transfer weights to HPU memory<br/>Habana Synapse API

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 2: Model Inference Request
    Client->>KServe: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS (platform TLS)
    KServe->>API: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8000 (internal)
    API->>Runner: Inference request (in-process)
    Runner->>HPU: Execute model graph<br/>Habana Synapse API
    HPU-->>Runner: Inference output

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 3: Distributed Inference (Tensor Parallel)
    Runner->>Peers: HCCL all-reduce / all-gather<br/>RDMA transport<br/>No encryption (cluster-internal)
    Peers-->>Runner: Synchronized tensors

    Runner-->>API: Prediction result (in-process)
    API-->>KServe: JSON response<br/>HTTP/8000
    KServe-->>Client: JSON response<br/>HTTPS (platform TLS)

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 4: KV Cache Transfer (NIXL Disaggregated)
    participant Prefill as Prefill Instance<br/>(NixlConnectorWorker)
    participant Decode as Decode Instance<br/>(NixlConnectorWorker)
    Prefill->>Prefill: HPU memory → CPU buffer<br/>(device-to-host copy)
    Prefill->>Decode: KV cache blocks<br/>NIXL protocol (RDMA/TCP)<br/>No encryption
    Decode->>Decode: CPU buffer → HPU KV cache<br/>(host-to-device copy)
